<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-jdvEJ1QgQjOADoQkuRHUSA" name=",_owvTIKMFEeCyK4sysVB96g" guid="-jdvEJ1QgQjOADoQkuRHUSA" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Annex C of ISO 26262, volume 6 provides information on strategies around tailoring the SW safety lifecycle for&#xD;
    configurable software. This is a normative section of the specification and it is advised that the user shall apply it&#xD;
    if using configurable software.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It covers reference phase process models for different configuration and calibration data, and deals with verification&#xD;
    of that data, so there are references to using the verification plan pattern from ISO 26262, volume. 8, clause 9.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To provide input to the safety plan based upon using configurable software.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
